headline.main: Few Changes Are Expected in the Onassis Empire

docs.lead_paragraph: LEAD: The sudden death of Christina Onassis in Argentina over the weekend presaged no changes in the shipping and real-estate empire founded by her father, Aristotle S. Onassis, according to several members of a multinational board that has run the business since he died in 1975.
